snippet.textDisplay:
You should also consider the issue that arises with "panic buying" in bulk. I don't know about you guys in the states but in canada there are a lot of grocery stores that have had their shelves cleaned out. Lots of people have been stocking up (over buying) on essentials which have resulted in a shortage of many things everybody needs.

Be considerate of the fact that other people might need things too. A few of my family friends have had to actually get food from neighbors because the stores are being picked clean and supplies hoarded. My own cupboards are very bare because the day before i usually shop, people started panicking and buying in bulk to stock up.

Where am i supposed to get food from if everyone keeps grabbing 15 to 20 things of pasta and soup? 5 toilet papers, soap, shampoo/ conditioner....all gone........Every day since Thursday the stores have been emptied of milk and water..... The bread is gone...the cereal is gone, peanut butter, flour, rice, meat.....being horded by people.

snippet.textDisplay: Im not trying to spread misinformation or anything, because I definitely agree it is better to be overprepared and the virus turns out to be nothing, rather than the alternative. However there is a fine line between being prepared and being stupid and I feel like a lot of people are crossing that line. You get to see how people really act in the apocalypse. Those that buy WAY too much water/toilet paper/supplies with no regard to what will be left to their fellow man. We need to stop these people. Cause what about the people who cant afford to stop going to work for a few weeks? What about the people who cant spare the money to buy all those extra supplies ahead of time? What about the people who were just a little to late to the punch and now everything is gone. There isnt enough supplies left to last a person 1 week, much less the 6 weeks that people tell you to stock up for. Meanwhile a bunch of people sit comfortably in their home with an entire years supply of this stuff. Its not ok. We need to do something about this.

snippet.textDisplay:
“The single quality that is common across every living creature on this planet, is fear; it’s funny then that as common as fear is, we so easily underestimate its power.

Fear of growing close to someone, the subsequent fear of loss, fear of failure; and as more people depend on you, those fears can take on greater power.

Fear itself isn’t worthy of concern, it is who we become while in its clutches . Will you be proud of that person? Will you forgive them? Will you understand why they felt the need to do the things they did? Will you even recognize them? Or will the person staring back at you be the very thing you should have feared from the start?

I suppose we all find out sooner or later. “
-Ozpin

I found this very fitting to what is going on. We should be concerned and serious about this virus, yes, but we shouldn’t let fear overtake us. We will all get through this, stay strong and healthy everyone! ❤️❤️❤️
